page.title: 08Freshfield's population
page.content:
From a random sample, in km square ref:{03300408,}taken one weekday morning, of 130 houses, 40 families had been there less than 5 years and 87 had lived there for more than 5 years. People had moved into the area mainly from Formby, Maghull, Wigan and Liverpool. Others came from Manchester, Sheffield, Scotland, Kent, Herts., Hants., Norwich, Dorset, and the West Midlands.
In another random sample, in km square ref:{03290408,}taken one weekday morning, 209 houses were visited and were inhabited by a total of 132 men, 133 women and 153 children.
